        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Two Giants of the Global Ginger Market</h2>
        <p>
          India is the world's largest ginger producer, harvesting roughly 2.2 million metric tons annually. Nigeria ranks as Africa's top producer and among the world's top five, with annual production of approximately 350,000-400,000 metric tons. Together, these two origins supply a significant share of international ginger trade.
        </p>
        <p>
          But volume only tells part of the story. The critical difference lies in what is inside the ginger root: the concentration of bioactive compounds that determine potency, flavor intensity, and suitability for different applications. This is where Nigerian ginger stands apart.
        </p>

